     <ab>Cf. N N47.41b (cf. <bibl>Kotwal and Kreyenbroek, 2003</bibl>: 216-7):</ab>
 <ab class="ab_indent"><em> ka pad </em>humatanąm<em>
be hilēd tā ān 4 </em>ẏaθā ahū vairiiō<em> ud</em> 3 aṣ̌əm vohū<em> *ōh dārišn</em></ab>
<ab class="ab_indent">If he (the <em>zōt</em>) has put (the fat on the bone) down (into the fire)at <em>humatanąm</em>, he has to hold it until the end of the four Ahuna Vairiia (Y41.9) and the three Aṣ̌əm Vohū (Y41.10). </ab>
   
